<br>
Well, I was in an EQ slump at the time anyways, so I figured I would just quit. But now, I wanted to come back...and I remembered about the station password retrieval thing off of everquest.com...I did it, and it worked, and now I have control of my account again...<br>
<br>
But sadly, everything except for my no drop items (about 4 things) are missing from my level 51 paladin. Obviously, I don't want to report this, because from what I last heard, they just cancel and delete your account on hacking issues. I want to try and restart, but I don't know where. I figured I could come here for help, since I've been following this board for over a year now. I know other paladins here have been hacked. How did you restart...or did you? All I have left for a weapon is my soulfire, and for armor I just have guardian from SS...Any help on what I could do would be appreciated. I'm a die-hard paladin player, and I hope to get back to my feet soon. If you play on my server (Bertoxxulous) and could lend me any advice, I would be grateful.<br>
<br>
Thanks for listening.<br>
<br>
Derrian <br>
51 Cavalier <br>
Bertoxxulous <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uketherami.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kether Am I</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 505<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(2/9/02 1:38:41 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=14414.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Need help (hacked)...</span><hr size=1> Although things may at first seem grim, if you still enjoy playing the game all is not lost.  <br>
<br>
The general EQ economy is such that it will take far less time to equip yourself to a reasonable PvE level than it would have a year ago.<br>
<br>
If you have some friends in game gathering a small loan for equipment (1k or so) will help field you in near full Ry'Gor armor.  If not, it will take a little more time, but not too much.<br>
<br>
Go to a green dungeon where you can kill swiftly and safely.  Preferably one where the creatures drop fine steel or some pp.  It shouldn't take long till you have enough to buy some ro/ry'gor/fine plate and a runic carver or similar weapon.  You don't *really* have to do this.  But it will help with the next step.<br>
<br>
Go XPing, preferable in 'pick-up' areas where the mobs aren't too challenging.  At this equip level you wouldn't make a very good tank, so try to fill the 5th or 6th spots in a group that already have a tank.  The reason you wanted some armor from the above step is to be slighly more respectable and survivable in battle.  I woulnd't mention that you were hacked, I would probably just say you sold all your goods for pp when you quit the game and gave to a friend.  He left, you are back, but now pennyless.  The easier camps at KC would be a good spot.  Get a level or so and more platinum, and maybe a rare drop.<br>
<br>
DW armor is cheap now.  I have seen all pieces save chest/legs for sale on E'ci for less than 2k each, with hands/helm/arm under 1k each.<br>
<br>
Another option is Icewell Keep.  But since the armor is the very near equivalent of Valo people have flocked to there and pester raids and swarm like vultures around armor drops.  And stories of being 'hacked' are common there.  So common that they are largely thought to be lies.  Unless you have friends that are doing the raiding I would suggest working up to a playable level on your own.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
Kether <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/unorpin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Norpin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 57<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(2/9/02 1:40:14 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=14414.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Need help (hacked)...</span><hr size=1> I think I'd start by farming Runnyeye for Blackened Alloy Armor.  Sporali Defender's Blade makes an ok 1hs and I think the Blackened Alloy Bastard Sword (24/39) is more damaging than the Soulfire.  That should give you enough AC to at least group or farm some of the harder stuff.<br>
<br>
I don't know whick slots you have filled...<br>
<br>
Hands: Farm Iksar Scaled Gloves from Warslik's Woods<br>
Wrist: Farm Bracer of Scavenging, also in WW<br>
Fingers: Farm Jagged Bands from Unrest<br>
Feet: Farm Dwarven Work Boots from Unrest<br>
Shoulders: Farm Bloodstained Mantle from Unrest<br>
Ears: Farm Cougars in Iceclad? for Cougar Claw Earrings<br>
Head: Farm Kunark Giants for a Lumberjack Cap (not WW)<br>
Waist: Farm Kunark Giants for Staw Spun Belt (not WW)<br>
<br>
Start grouping in Lower Guk to try and get a FBSS, SSB, and EBC.  After that I guess head for KC and OS to try and get Deepwater.  Sign up for as many plane raids as you can to try and get some decent Ac gear.<br>
<br>
The hardest part will be getting a good weapon I think.  I guess you could try to get a Arbitor's Combine Greatsword from OS or try to get a Argent Defender on a Chardok Royals raid.<br>
<br>
Edit: There's also Strength of Grodan from ME.  41/51 2hs with +25str and +10 sta.  No drop, but not too rare I hear. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/unorpin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Norpin</A> at: 2/10/02 5:50:19 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uavalssra.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Avalssra</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 50<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(2/9/02 2:49:02 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=14414.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Need help (hacked)...</span><hr size=1> Id also consider not changing the payment info on your acount. Since its someone elses creditcard paying for the account and they no longer have the access to change it.<br>
